# Final Parking Lot LLD Review & Corrections

## 🛠️ Code Fixes Implemented
I have applied the following fixes to your code to handle Concurrency correctly.

### 1. Atomic Locking in [ParkingSpot.java](file:///c:/Users/satya/Desktop/lld/ParkingLot/entities/ParkingSpot.java)
I changed [park()](file:///c:/Users/satya/Desktop/lld/ParkingLot/entities/ParkingSpot.java#21-29) from `void` to `boolean`. This allows the spot to "refuse" checking in if another thread occupied it *microseconds* before.

```java
// Entity: ParkingSpot
public synchronized boolean park(Vehicle vehicle) {
    if (isOccupied) {
        return false; // Critical: Check inside the lock!
    }
    this.vehicle = vehicle;
    this.isOccupied = true;
    return true;
}
```

### 2. Optimistic Checking in [ParkingSystem.java](file:///c:/Users/satya/Desktop/lld/ParkingLot/ParkingSystem.java)
In your `Main` class or System, we now check the result. Your previous attempt with `synchronized(this)` on the system had a **scope error** (Ticket was defined inside the block but used outside) and locked the *wrong object* (locking the system doesn't stop two threads from *finding* the same spot).

```java
// System: parkVehicle
entities.ParkingSpot spot = parkingStrategy.findParkingSpot(vehicle, levels);

// Optimistic Locking: Try to park. 
// If `park()` returns true, we won the race. 
// If false, another thread took this spot between 'find' and 'park'.
if (spot != null && spot.park(vehicle)) {
    Ticket ticket = new Ticket(...);
    parkedVehicles.put(vehicle.licensePlate, ticket);
    return ticket;
}
// Logic Note: In a real system, you would loop here to find the NEXT available spot.
return null;
```

